vulnerability.name: USN-3022-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that LibreOffice incorrectly handled RTF document files. If a user were tricked into opening a specially crafted RTF document, a remote attacker could cause LibreOffice to crash, and possibly execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: LibreOffice could be made to crash or run programs as your login if it opened a specially crafted file.
